OL,3,CResearch may shed light on difficulty
OL,4,Cin identifying The Traitors
OL,6,FPostgraduate student Fiammetta Marini
OL,7,Fexplained: "We know that we
OL,8,Fsubconsciously judge whether an
OL,9,Findividual is trustworthy based on
OL,10,Ffacial characteristics.
OL,12,F"For example, high eyebrows that seem
OL,13,Fsurprised-looking in their shape,
OL,14,Falong with a U-shaped mouth, are
OL,15,Fusually perceived as trustworthy.
OL,17,F"On the other hand, eyes close
OL,18,Ftogether or lower eyebrows are often
OL,19,Fperceived as untrustworthy.
OL,26,@oD@LOUtD@AOUyD@AOU
