OL,3,CResearch may shed light on difficulty
OL,4,Cin identifying The Traitors
OL,6,F"Regardless, we make these split-
OL,7,Fsecond judgments and they have a big
OL,8,Fimpact in our everyday lives, even if
OL,9,Fthese impressions are not always
OL,10,Faccurate, they invariably shape our
OL,11,Fsocial behaviour."
OL,13,FMs Marini and her research colleagues
OL,14,Ffound that rather than examining every
OL,15,Findividual face, our visual system
OL,16,Fblends the trustworthiness impressions
OL,17,Fof an entire group of faces into an
OL,18,Faverage representation that gives us
OL,19,Fan immediate gist.
